FT  26 FEB 93 / World News in Brief: Sellafield radiation leak
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Nuclear Fuels reported another radiation leak at the Sellafield
plant in Cumbria. The company said above-normal levels of iodine 129 in
discharges from a ventilation stack posed no danger to workers or nearby
residents. There was a plutonium leak at the plant earlier this month.
