<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 93 / The Property Market: Investment Property Databank's figures
indicates hint of market improvement
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THERE WAS a hint of improvement in the market in January, according to the
Investment Property Databank's latest monthly figures.
January saw the lowest monthly fall in capital values recorded since last
July - by just over half a point - the result of a further outward shift in
yields and the continued decline in rental values.
Total return for January stood at 0.2 per cent, an increase from the zero
return recorded in December.
But the year-on-year results continued to fall. Rents fell by more than 10
per cent in the year to January, while capital growth and total return fell
to -8.5 per cent and -0.2 per cent, respectively.
Offices and industrials showed a relative improvement in their monthly
returns of four and five basis points respectively, while those for the
retail sector remained static, at 0.3 per cent.
The industrial sector showed the strongest monthly return, beating retails
for the first time since January 1992.
A slight deterioration in capital values, to -0.4 per cent, meant that total
return for the retail sector remained at 0.3 per cent for the month.
Office values improved by about half a point in January, representing their
highest monthly return since early 1990.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
