<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 93 / International Company News: American International Group
reports after-tax profits of dollars 458.9m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AMERICAN International Group yesterday reported after-tax profits of Dollars
458.9m in the fourth quarter of 1992, up from Dollars 399.8m in the same
period of 1991. The figures included realised capital gains of Dollars 13.2m
and Dollars 10.3m respectively, writes Nikki Tait in New York.
The quarter's results take AIG's net profits total for the year to Dollars
1.66bn, against Dollars 1.55bn in 1991. The 1992 figure includes realised
capital gains of Dollars 64.2m, up from Dollars 60.7m in the 1991, and a
Dollars 31.9m boost from accounting changes.
The insurer noted that, like most of the industry, it had been badly hit by
catastrophe losses last year - to the tune of over Dollars 190m  - but
attributed the results to the spread of its business.
For the year overall, AIG's general insurance division produced operating
profits of Dollars 1.12bn, a decline of 9.9 per cent from 1991's Dollars
1.25bn. Feeling the impact of catastrophe losses, the underwriting deficit
rose from Dollars 4.8m to Dollars 195m, while net investment income
increased from Dollars 1.16bn to Dollars 1.25bn.
On the life insurance side, operating profits rose from Dollars 561.8m to
Dollars 667.4m, while the financial services division overall made an
operating profit of Dollars 346.4m, up from Dollars 222.2m.
</TEXT>
