and chief financial officer of Astra, the leading Swedish pharmaceutical
group, writes Christopher Brown-Humes.
His departure stems from a personal disagreement with Mr Hakan Mogren, Astra
chief executive, over the future division of responsibilities. Neither the
company nor Dr Sjostrand were willing to elaborate.
Dr Sjostrand, 46, joined Astra in 1975 and has been on the group's executive
committee for the past 15 years. He was secretary of the board between 1976
and 1988 and a deputy of the board since then.
