there was scope for making progress in taking practical steps to cut
opportunities for crime.
In a letter to Mr Kenneth Clarke, the home secretary, he urged a renewed
emphasis on crime prevention, and in particular 'plastic fraud'. Losses from
credit cards and cheque guarantee cards had risen to Pounds 166m in 1991, he
said, an increase of one-third over the 1990 figure of Pounds 123m.
