FT  26 FEB 93 / Parliament and Politics: Labour rounds on Tories over jobs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RALPH ATKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GOVERNMENT ministers were accused by Labour last night of encouraging a
'climate of fear' over unemployment, homelessness and business failures,
that lay 'at the root' of Britain's economic and social problems', Ralph
Atkins writes.
As Labour intensified its campaign against unemployment Mrs Margaret
Beckett, the party's deputy leader, said Britain 'should be planning to
prosper, and not just struggling to get by.'
At a rally in Swindon she linked rising joblessness and crime, saying the
Conservatives 'have encouraged us to abandon our basic sense of shared
concern, of responsibility one for another.'
Labour plans further rallies in Tory marginal seats where unemployment has
risen dramatically.
