<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 93 / Property company sues council
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SLOUGH Estates, the property company that owns the Howard shopping centre in
Welwyn Garden City, Hertfordshire, is suing Welwyn Hatfield Council for more
than Pounds 20m,
The dispute involves the Gallerias, a rival shopping centre at Hatfield. The
council said it would vigorously defend the action.
Slough says that in 1987 the council deliberately concealed plans to relax
restrictions on the type of tenants at the Gallerias. This complex was
originally intended to be a specialist leisure centre, with no fashion,
convenience or food shops, but the developer persuaded the council to allow
it greater flexibility.
Slough says it would not have built the Howard centre if it had known the
Gallerias would be able to attract similar tenants. The Gallerias went into
receivership last September.
