<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 93 / Britain and US are bright spots in bleak global economy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain and the US are among the few bright spots in a bleak global economy,
according to the latest quarterly worldwide survey of business optimism from
Dun &amp; Bradstreet, the business information group.
The survey of 11,000 executives in 16 countries recorded a sharp increase in
sales and profits expectations for the first quarter of this year among
managers in Britain, while hopes in the US were steady at a relatively high
level. However, in Europe as a whole first quarter sales expectations fell
to their lowest level since D&amp;B began polling in 1988. The Japanese survey
was the gloomiest since 1990.
