<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 93 / London Stock Exchange: Equity Futures and Options Trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
STOCK index futures traded in a tight range of 20 points for most of the
day, as the market waited to see if ICI will launch an anticipated Pounds
1bn rights issue with its demerger plans, writes Joel Kibazo.
The March contract on the FT-SE opened at 2,819, just ahead of its close on
Tuesday. After a period of sideways trading, the contract started drifting
lower as the talk of the possible ICI cash call increased.
The day's low of 2,810 was seen only 45 minutes after the start of trading,
before a bout of closing of positions led to a brief respite in the downward
trend.
That, however, did not last long and March once again drifted downwards with
the early strength on Wall Street having no impact.
March finished at 2,818, at the same level as its close on Tuesday and at a
small discount to the underlying cash market. Turnover was 8,037 trades by
the close.
In traded options, the expiry of the February stock options was the main
feature and it made a large contribution to the day's total turnover of
41,189 lots. Some 7,378 contracts were dealt in the FT-SE 100 option, and
the Euro-FT-SE saw a total of 2,890 trades.
BT was the most actively dealt stock option with a total of 4,450 contracts
and was followed by BTR at 3,243. Hanson, Asda and British Aerospace were
also busy.
</TEXT>
