<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 93 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
GOLD shares recovered some of the losses made earlier this week on a firmer
bullion price and the index ended 19 higher at 1,027, although volume was
reported to be low. The overall index lost 9 to 3,438 and industrials eased
1 to 4,502.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>ZAZ  South Africa, Africa.
</CN>
