</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE depressed South African economy and industrial action caused earnings at
Murray and Roberts, the construction, engineering and supplies group, to
fall in the six months to the end of December.
Turnover rose 23 per cent to R3.27bn (Dollars 1.04bn) from R2.65bn, but this
